<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='348567' id='t-348567'>and over time they can get smarter.</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 6:03
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='352192' id='t-352192'>Look what happened: in this study,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='354993' id='t-354993'>students who were not
taught this growth mindset</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='358592' id='t-358592'>continued to show declining grades
over this difficult school transition,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='364223' id='t-364223'>but those who were taught this lesson
showed a sharp rebound in their grades.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='371187' id='t-371187'>We have shown this now,
this kind of improvement,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='377302' id='t-377302'>with thousands and thousands of kids,
especially struggling students.</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 6:34
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='383839' id='t-383839'>So let's talk about equality.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='388291' id='t-388291'>In our country, there are
groups of students</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='392553' id='t-392553'>who chronically underperform,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='395372' id='t-395372'>for example, children in inner cities,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='398354' id='t-398354'>or children on 
Native American reservations.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='402197' id='t-402197'>And they've done so poorly for so long
that many people think it's inevitable.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='409043' id='t-409043'>But when educators create
growth mindset classrooms steeped in yet,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='417442' id='t-417442'>equality happens.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='420727' id='t-420727'>And here are just a few examples.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='425027' id='t-425027'>In one year, a kindergarten class
in Harlem, New York</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='431157' id='t-431157'>scored in the 95th percentile
on the National Achievement Test.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='438634' id='t-438634'>Many of those kids could not hold a pencil
when they arrived at school.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='445872' id='t-445872'>In one year,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='448126' id='t-448126'>fourth grade students 
in the South Bronx, way behind,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='453497' id='t-453497'>became the number one fourth grade class
in the state of New York</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='459266' id='t-459266'>on the state math test.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='463240' id='t-463240'>In a year to a year and a half,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='467179' id='t-467179'>Native American students
